node.statement: COUPLING CONSTRAINT: From G_r(z) = G_p(omega_p(z)) and G_r(z) = G_q(omega_q(z)), the functions omega_p and omega_q are coupled. Specifically, omega_p(z) + omega_q(z) = z + F_r(z) where F_r depends only on r (not on the decomposition into p,q). This is the finite analog of the free additive subordination identity. The coupling constrains the joint distribution of (alpha, beta) corrections.
